      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "It's easy to come up with fallacious arguments for a proposition, whether true or false. What can be hard is to find a cogent argument for it, even when it's true. For example, it's now believed by mathematicians that the proposition known as \"Fermat's last theorem\" is true, yet it took over three centuries for anyone to prove it. In the meantime, many invalid arguments were presented for it.",
